usage_msg = """\

NAME
    fhold - manage under-review flags and concurrent-write permits

SYNOPSIS
    fhold {review|permit} register FILE [--agent ID] [--task TEXT]
    fhold {review|permit} release FILE [--agent ID]
    fhold {review|permit} check FILE
    fhold status FILE
    fhold gc [--tag-root DIR]

DESCRIPTION
    If a given file is being updated by only one AI agent, then the user wants
    to review the diff in their IDE. But if the file is being updated by 
    multiple AI agents, then IDE diff reviewing can clobber changes by other agents.
    fhold allows agents to coordinate, so the user can review diffs when only
    one agent is active on the file, but switch to safe unreviewed parallel writes
    when multiple agents are active.

    safewrite is a sibling utility that lets agents do such unreviewed parallel
    writes.  It enables parallel writes, at the price of bypassing the fhold
    system by which IDEs offer review of agent changes.

    fhold lets agents coordinate which mode to use. Agents
    register their intention about the file, detect when their intentions
    collide, and let the user choose.

    Agents can register two kinds of holds:

    review (review_hold) — exclusive. The agent's changes are on
    disk but awaiting review. If the user rejects any, the IDE reverts all
    changes made after those writes. The IDE may or may not detect the
    conflict on its own, and typically handles it poorly.

    permit (concurrent_write_permit) — non-exclusive. The user authorized
    unreviewed parallel writes when the agent registered this permit.
    Multiple agents may hold permits simultaneously. No agent should make
    IDE-reviewed writes while any permit exists for the file.

    Holds are implemented as sidecar tag files under --tag-root
    (default: /tmp/fhold.tags/). Each file is keyed by sha256 of the
    resolved target path (same scheme as safewrite locks).
    Ephemeral; cleared on reboot.

    The author's practice is to apply fhold only to git-tracked markdown files.

SUBCOMMANDS
    review register FILE  Tag FILE with review_hold. Atomic
                          (O_CREAT|O_EXCL). Fails if a review hold already
                          exists (contention). Records agent, task, timestamp,
                          and pre-write sha256.
    review release FILE   Remove the review_hold tag from FILE.
                          Typically called after the user accepts or rejects
                          the IDE diff.
    review check FILE     Print review hold status: owner agent, task, age,
                          whether post-write hash is set, and whether stale.
    permit register FILE  Tag FILE with concurrent_write_permit for this agent.
                          Multiple permit holds may coexist. Any permit hold
                          present = unreviewed mode.
    permit release FILE   Remove this agent's concurrent_write_permit tag.
                          When all permit holds are gone, review mode resumes
                          automatically.
    permit check FILE     List all active permit holds for FILE with agent IDs
                          and last-activity times.
    status FILE           Summary: review hold state, active permit holds,
                          current mode (reviewed / unreviewed), and file sha256.
    gc                    Garbage-collect stale review holds (TTL expired, no
                          heartbeat) and stale permit holds (mtime > TTL).

OPTIONS
    --agent ID            Agent/session identifier. Default: $WIBEY_SESSION_ID
                          or $USER.
    --task TEXT            One-line description stored in the review hold
                          (review register only).
    --tag-root DIR        Tag directory (default: /tmp/fhold.tags/).
    --ttl SECS            Stale hold TTL in seconds (default: 1800).

    -H, --raw-help        Show this raw usage text and exit
    -h, --help            Show colorized usage and exit

EXIT CODES
    0  success
    1  usage error (bad arguments)
    2  contention — review hold already held by another agent
                   (review register only)
    3  no hold found (release of nonexistent hold)

MENU
    An agent should show this menu to the user when it encounters
    a review hold registered by another agent.

    [FILE] has a review hold from another agent. Resolve or ignore the
    other agent's under-review changes, then indicate your decision:

    Diff resolved, stay in review mode — This agent will claim the
        review hold and write its changes for review. (Future agents who
        find a review hold when attempting a write will similarly offer to
        claim the hold.)

    Diff resolved, switch to unreviewed mode — This agent will start doing
        its writes without user review. Other agents that attempt writes
        will recognize that they too should start writing without user review.
        All parallel writes will be safe if the agents use e.g. safewrite.
        Enjoy your safe multi-agent workflow!

    Diff ignored, switch to unreviewed mode — Current on-disk state will be
        treated as accepted. Agents will proceed as in the previous option.
        WARNING: The pending diff can still be safely accepted at any time,
        but in some IDEs rejecting any part of it will overwrite
        any changes that were saved after that pending diff was authored.
        Those IDEs may or may not warn you that saved changes will be discarded.
        So your smart play is to resolve the other agent's changes first.

EXAMPLES
    # REVIEW MODE: Agent 1 gets clearance to make solo diff-reviewed edits
    $ fhold review register README.md --agent claude1 --task "update install steps"
    /tmp/fhold.tags/_users_fred_myrepo_README.md_36885306.review_hold
    # Agent 1 makes solo edits, which appear as diffs in IDE. User reviews...
    # ...User stops working on the file, review hold expires after 30mins. Or....

    # PERMIT MODE: User asks Agent 2 to also edit the file. Agent 2 requests a review_hold:
    $ fhold review register README.md --agent claude2 --task "add examples"
    fhold: exit 2 — review_hold exists: agent=claude1 task="update install steps" age=4m
    # Agent 2 shows the user the Menu (see MENU) and waits for a choice
    # User resolves Agent 1 diffs and then picks "Diff resolved, switch to unreviewed mode"
    # Agent 2 cancels Agent 1's hold, then registers a permit:
    $ fhold review release README.md
    $ fhold permit register README.md --agent claude2
    /tmp/fhold.tags/_users_fred_myrepo_README.md_36885306.concurrent_write_permit.claude2
    # Agent 2 proceeds to make unreviewed concurrent edits using e.g. safewrite

    # As usual, Agent 1 checks status before its next reviewed write and gets a surprise:
    $ fhold status README.md
    mode: unreviewed (1 permit hold: claude2)
    # Agent 1 sees the file is now in permit mode, and so requests a permit:
    $ fhold permit register README.md --agent claude1
    /tmp/fhold.tags/_private_myrepo_README.md_36885306.concurrent_write_permit.claude1
    # Agent 1 proceeds to make unreviewed concurrent edits using e.g. safewrite

    # Permits expire 30mins after creation, or agents can explicitly release their permits:
    $ fhold permit release README.md --agent claude1
    # When no valid permits exist, the file defaults to review mode:
    $ fhold status README.md
    mode: reviewed (no holds)
"""

# usage_msg is intentionally placed at the very top for human readers and future agents.
# usage_msg formatting and content ALWAYS trumps show_usage(). If you change usage_msg,
# you MUST update show_usage() to match it EXACTLY, including newlines and spacing.
# Agents must not update usage_msg without explicit instructions to do so.
# When they aren't in sync, agents must update show_usage()'s underlying
# non-colorized text to match usage_msg, while keeping all colorization intact.

import hashlib
import json
import os
import re
import subprocess
import sys
import time
from datetime import datetime, timezone
from pathlib import Path
from typing import Optional


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Key generation (same pattern as safewrite)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

def _fakepath(path: Path) -> str:
    """Generate tag key: try fakepath utility, fallback to sha256 hash."""
    try:
        result = subprocess.run(
            ["fakepath", str(path)],
            capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=5,
        )
        if result.returncode == 0:
            return result.stdout.strip()
    except Exception:
        pass
    # Fallback: resolve without strict so nonexistent files still work
    return hashlib.sha256(str(path.resolve()).encode()).hexdigest()[:24]


def _sha256_of_file(path: Path) -> str:
    """SHA-256 of file content, or sha256('') if file doesn't exist."""
    if not path.exists():
        return hashlib.sha256(b"").hexdigest()
    return hashlib.sha256(path.read_bytes()).hexdigest()


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tag file helpers
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

def _ensure_tag_root(tag_root: Path) -> None:
    tag_root.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)


def _review_hold_path(tag_root: Path, target: Path) -> Path:
    key = _fakepath(target)
    return tag_root / f"{key}.review_hold"


def _permit_path(tag_root: Path, target: Path, agent: str) -> Path:
    key = _fakepath(target)
    return tag_root / f"{key}.concurrent_write_permit.{agent}"


def _find_permits(tag_root: Path, target: Path) -> list[Path]:
    """Find all permit tags for a given target file."""
    if not tag_root.exists():
        return []
    key = _fakepath(target)
    prefix = f"{key}.concurrent_write_permit."
    return sorted(p for p in tag_root.iterdir() if p.name.startswith(prefix))


def _read_tag(path: Path) -> Optional[dict]:
    try:
        return json.loads(path.read_text(encoding="utf-8"))
    except Exception:
        return None


def _write_tag(path: Path, meta: dict) -> None:
    path.write_text(json.dumps(meta, indent=2, sort_keys=True), encoding="utf-8")


def _format_age(seconds: float) -> str:
    if seconds < 60:
        return f"{int(seconds)}s"
    if seconds < 3600:
        return f"{int(seconds / 60)}m"
    return f"{seconds / 3600:.1f}h"


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Subcommand implementations
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

def cmd_review_register(target: Path, agent: str, task: str, tag_root: Path) -> int:
    _ensure_tag_root(tag_root)
    hold_path = _review_hold_path(tag_root, target)

    # Check for existing hold
    if hold_path.exists():
        existing = _read_tag(hold_path)
        existing_agent = (existing or {}).get("agent", "unknown")
        # Same agent re-registering: update in place
        if existing_agent == agent:
            meta = existing or {}
            meta["task"] = task
            meta["acquired"] = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()
            meta["pre_write_sha256"] = _sha256_of_file(target)
            _write_tag(hold_path, meta)
            print(str(hold_path))
            return 0
        # Different agent: contention
        existing_task = (existing or {}).get("task", "")
        acquired = (existing or {}).get("acquired", "unknown")
        age_s = 0.0
        try:
            age_s = time.time() - hold_path.stat().st_mtime
        except Exception:
            pass
        task_part = f' task="{existing_task}"' if existing_task else ""
        print(
            f"fhold: exit 2 — review_hold exists: agent={existing_agent}"
            f"{task_part} age={_format_age(age_s)}",
            file=sys.stderr,
        )
        return 2

    # Create atomically
    meta = {
        "agent": agent,
        "file": str(target),
        "task": task,
        "acquired": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
        "pre_write_sha256": _sha256_of_file(target),
    }
    try:
        fd = os.open(str(hold_path), os.O_CREAT | os.O_EXCL | os.O_WRONLY, 0o644)
        os.write(fd, json.dumps(meta, indent=2, sort_keys=True).encode("utf-8"))
        os.close(fd)
    except FileExistsError:
        # Race: another agent created it between our check and open
        existing = _read_tag(hold_path)
        existing_agent = (existing or {}).get("agent", "unknown")
        existing_task = (existing or {}).get("task", "")
        task_part = f' task="{existing_task}"' if existing_task else ""
        print(
            f"fhold: exit 2 — review_hold exists: agent={existing_agent}{task_part}",
            file=sys.stderr,
        )
        return 2

    print(str(hold_path))
    return 0


def cmd_review_release(target: Path, tag_root: Path) -> int:
    hold_path = _review_hold_path(tag_root, target)
    if not hold_path.exists():
        print(f"fhold: no review hold found for {target}", file=sys.stderr)
        return 3
    hold_path.unlink()
    return 0


def cmd_review_check(target: Path, tag_root: Path) -> int:
    hold_path = _review_hold_path(tag_root, target)
    if not hold_path.exists():
        print(f"fhold: no review hold found for {target}", file=sys.stderr)
        return 3
    meta = _read_tag(hold_path)
    if not meta:
        print(f"fhold: review hold tag unreadable at {hold_path}", file=sys.stderr)
        return 3
    agent = meta.get("agent", "unknown")
    task = meta.get("task", "")
    acquired = meta.get("acquired", "unknown")
    pre_hash = meta.get("pre_write_sha256", "")
    post_hash = meta.get("post_write_sha256", "")
    age_s = 0.0
    try:
        age_s = time.time() - hold_path.stat().st_mtime
    except Exception:
        pass
    print(f"review_hold: agent={agent} task=\"{task}\" acquired={acquired} age={_format_age(age_s)}")
    if pre_hash:
        print(f"  pre_write_sha256: {pre_hash}")
    if post_hash:
        print(f"  post_write_sha256: {post_hash}")
    return 0


def cmd_permit_register(target: Path, agent: str, tag_root: Path) -> int:
    _ensure_tag_root(tag_root)
    permit_path = _permit_path(tag_root, target, agent)
    meta = {
        "agent": agent,
        "file": str(target),
        "acquired": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
    }
    _write_tag(permit_path, meta)
    print(str(permit_path))
    return 0


def cmd_permit_release(target: Path, agent: str, tag_root: Path) -> int:
    permit_path = _permit_path(tag_root, target, agent)
    if not permit_path.exists():
        print(f"fhold: no permit hold found for agent={agent} on {target}", file=sys.stderr)
        return 3
    permit_path.unlink()
    return 0


def cmd_permit_check(target: Path, tag_root: Path) -> int:
    permits = _find_permits(tag_root, target)
    if not permits:
        print(f"fhold: no permit holds found for {target}", file=sys.stderr)
        return 3
    for p in permits:
        meta = _read_tag(p)
        agent = (meta or {}).get("agent", p.name.rsplit(".", 1)[-1])
        age_s = 0.0
        try:
            age_s = time.time() - p.stat().st_mtime
        except Exception:
            pass
        acquired = (meta or {}).get("acquired", "unknown")
        print(f"  permit: agent={agent} acquired={acquired} age={_format_age(age_s)}")
    return 0


def cmd_status(target: Path, tag_root: Path, ttl: int) -> int:
    _ensure_tag_root(tag_root)
    hold_path = _review_hold_path(tag_root, target)
    permits = _find_permits(tag_root, target)
    file_hash = _sha256_of_file(target)

    has_review = hold_path.exists()
    review_meta = _read_tag(hold_path) if has_review else None

    if permits:
        agents = []
        for p in permits:
            meta = _read_tag(p)
            agents.append((meta or {}).get("agent", p.name.rsplit(".", 1)[-1]))
        agent_list = ", ".join(agents)
        print(f"mode: unreviewed ({len(permits)} permit hold{'s' if len(permits) != 1 else ''}: {agent_list})")
    elif has_review:
        agent = (review_meta or {}).get("agent", "unknown")
        task = (review_meta or {}).get("task", "")
        age_s = 0.0
        try:
            age_s = time.time() - hold_path.stat().st_mtime
        except Exception:
            pass
        task_part = f' task="{task}"' if task else ""
        print(f"mode: reviewed (review hold: agent={agent}{task_part} age={_format_age(age_s)})")
    else:
        print("mode: reviewed (no holds)")

    print(f"sha256: {file_hash}")
    return 0


def cmd_gc(tag_root: Path, ttl: int) -> int:
    if not tag_root.exists():
        return 0
    now = time.time()
    removed = 0
    for tag_file in sorted(tag_root.iterdir()):
        if not tag_file.is_file():
            continue
        is_review = tag_file.name.endswith(".review_hold")
        is_permit = ".concurrent_write_permit." in tag_file.name
        if not is_review and not is_permit:
            continue
        try:
            age_s = now - tag_file.stat().st_mtime
        except Exception:
            continue
        if age_s > ttl:
            meta = _read_tag(tag_file)
            agent = (meta or {}).get("agent", "unknown")
            kind = "review_hold" if is_review else "permit"
            print(f"gc: removed stale {kind} (agent={agent}, age={_format_age(age_s)}): {tag_file.name}")
            tag_file.unlink()
            removed += 1
    if removed:
        print(f"gc: removed {removed} stale tag{'s' if removed != 1 else ''}")
    return 0


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Argument parsing
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

def _default_agent() -> str:
    return os.environ.get("WIBEY_SESSION_ID", os.environ.get("USER", "unknown"))


def show_usage() -> None:
    RESET = "\033[0m"
    BOLD = "\033[1m"
    UNDERLINE = "\033[4m"
    ITALIC = "\033[3m"
    CMD = "\033[1;34m"
    FLAG = "\033[1;36m"
    FS_VAR = "\033[32m"
    FS_LIT = "\033[1;32m"
    ARG_VAR = "\033[33m"
    ARG_LIT = "\033[1;33m"
    FF_VAR = "\033[35m"

    section_titles = {
        "NAME",
        "SYNOPSIS",
        "DESCRIPTION",
        "SUBCOMMANDS",
        "OPTIONS",
        "EXIT CODES",
        "MENU",
        "EXAMPLES",
    }

    def cmd(s: str) -> str:
        return f"{CMD}{s}{RESET}"

    def flag(s: str) -> str:
        return f"{FLAG}{s}{RESET}"

    def fs_var(s: str) -> str:
        return f"{FS_VAR}{UNDERLINE}{ITALIC}{s}{RESET}"

    def fs_lit(s: str) -> str:
        return f"{FS_LIT}{UNDERLINE}{s}{RESET}"

    def arg_var(s: str) -> str:
        return f"{ARG_VAR}{ITALIC}{s}{RESET}"

    def arg_lit(s: str) -> str:
        return f"{ARG_LIT}{s}{RESET}"

    def ff_var(s: str) -> str:
        return f"{FF_VAR}{ITALIC}{s}{RESET}"

    command_words = ("fhold", "safewrite", "fakepath", "shasum", "awk")
    fs_var_words = ("FILE", "DIR")
    ff_var_words = ("ID", "TEXT", "TASK")
    arg_var_words = ("SECS",)
    fs_lits = ("/tmp/fhold.tags/",)

    def _style_line(line: str) -> str:
        if line.strip() in section_titles:
            return f"{BOLD}{UNDERLINE}{line}{RESET}"

        styled = line

        # Protect filesystem literals from later regex-based styling.
        literal_placeholders: dict[str, str] = {}
        for idx, lit in enumerate(fs_lits):
            placeholder = f"__FS_LIT_{idx}__"
            if lit in styled:
                styled = styled.replace(lit, placeholder)
                literal_placeholders[placeholder] = fs_lit(lit)

        # Commands.
        for w in command_words:
            styled = re.sub(rf"\b{re.escape(w)}\b", cmd(w), styled)

        # Flags.
        styled = re.sub(r"--[a-zA-Z0-9-]+", lambda m: flag(m.group(0)), styled)
        styled = re.sub(r"(?<!\S)-[A-Za-z](?=[,\s]|$)", lambda m: flag(m.group(0)), styled)

        # Placeholder variables by category.
        for w in fs_var_words:
            styled = re.sub(rf"\b{re.escape(w)}\b", fs_var(w), styled)
        for w in ff_var_words:
            styled = re.sub(rf"\b{re.escape(w)}\b", ff_var(w), styled)
        for w in arg_var_words:
            styled = re.sub(rf"\b{re.escape(w)}\b", arg_var(w), styled)

        # Exit code literals.
        styled = re.sub(r"(?<=\s)([0-9])(?=\s{2,})", lambda m: arg_lit(m.group(1)), styled)

        # Restore filesystem literals after other substitutions.
        for placeholder, rendered in literal_placeholders.items():
            styled = styled.replace(placeholder, rendered)
        return styled

    for line in usage_msg.splitlines(keepends=True):
        newline = ""
        body = line
        if line.endswith("\n"):
            newline = "\n"
            body = line[:-1]
        sys.stdout.write(_style_line(body) + newline)


def main() -> int:
    # Pre-scan for help flags only in the first argument position to avoid
    # false positives when -h/-H appear as option values.
    if len(sys.argv) > 1 and sys.argv[1] in ("-H", "--raw-help"):
        sys.stdout.write(usage_msg)
        return 0
    if len(sys.argv) > 1 and sys.argv[1] in ("-h", "--help"):
        show_usage()
        return 0

    # Parse arguments manually since the command structure is:
    #   fhold {review|permit} {register|release|check} FILE [options]
    #   fhold status FILE [options]
    #   fhold gc [options]
    args = sys.argv[1:]
    if not args:
        print("usage: fhold {review|permit} {register|release|check} FILE [options]", file=sys.stderr)
        print("       fhold status FILE [options]", file=sys.stderr)
        print("       fhold gc [options]", file=sys.stderr)
        print("Run 'fhold -h' for help.", file=sys.stderr)
        return 1

    # Extract global options from anywhere in args
    tag_root_str = "/tmp/fhold.tags/"
    ttl = 1800
    agent = _default_agent()
    task = ""

    # Pull out known flags
    positional: list[str] = []
    i = 0
    while i < len(args):
        if args[i] == "--tag-root" and i + 1 < len(args):
            tag_root_str = args[i + 1]
            i += 2
        elif args[i] == "--ttl" and i + 1 < len(args):
            try:
                ttl = int(args[i + 1])
            except ValueError:
                print(f"fhold: invalid --ttl value: {args[i + 1]}", file=sys.stderr)
                return 1
            i += 2
        elif args[i] == "--agent" and i + 1 < len(args):
            agent = args[i + 1]
            i += 2
        elif args[i] == "--task" and i + 1 < len(args):
            task = args[i + 1]
            i += 2
        else:
            positional.append(args[i])
            i += 1

    tag_root = Path(tag_root_str).expanduser()

    # Route subcommands
    if not positional:
        print("fhold: missing subcommand", file=sys.stderr)
        return 1

    subcmd = positional[0]

    if subcmd == "gc":
        return cmd_gc(tag_root, ttl)

    if subcmd == "status":
        if len(positional) < 2:
            print("fhold: status requires FILE argument", file=sys.stderr)
            return 1
        target = Path(positional[1]).expanduser()
        return cmd_status(target, tag_root, ttl)

    if subcmd in ("review", "permit"):
        if len(positional) < 2:
            print(f"fhold: {subcmd} requires an action (register|release|check)", file=sys.stderr)
            return 1
        action = positional[1]
        if action not in ("register", "release", "check"):
            print(f"fhold: unknown action '{action}' for {subcmd}", file=sys.stderr)
            return 1
        if action == "check":
            if len(positional) < 3:
                print(f"fhold: {subcmd} check requires FILE argument", file=sys.stderr)
                return 1
            target = Path(positional[2]).expanduser()
            if subcmd == "review":
                return cmd_review_check(target, tag_root)
            else:
                return cmd_permit_check(target, tag_root)

        if action == "register":
            if len(positional) < 3:
                print(f"fhold: {subcmd} register requires FILE argument", file=sys.stderr)
                return 1
            target = Path(positional[2]).expanduser()
            if subcmd == "review":
                return cmd_review_register(target, agent, task, tag_root)
            else:
                return cmd_permit_register(target, agent, tag_root)

        if action == "release":
            if len(positional) < 3:
                print(f"fhold: {subcmd} release requires FILE argument", file=sys.stderr)
                return 1
            target = Path(positional[2]).expanduser()
            if subcmd == "review":
                return cmd_review_release(target, tag_root)
            else:
                return cmd_permit_release(target, agent, tag_root)

    print(f"fhold: unknown subcommand '{subcmd}'", file=sys.stderr)
    return 1


if __name__ == "__main__":
    sys.exit(main())
